                        "value": "Scope and Contents"
                    }
                ],
                "p": [
                    {
                        "value": "This collection consists of photocopies of outgoing letters from Samuel \"Chip\" Delany to various correspondents, including Robert S. Bravard and Joanna Russ, in 1983 and 1984. Topics covered in the letters include daily life in New York City, childhood memories, literary criticism, HIV and AIDS during the 1980s, science fiction as a literary genre, and science fiction conventions."
                    },
                    {
                        "value": "An undated portrait of Delaney is also included."
                    }
                ]
